---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="Data Deletion - BrewOS"
  description="Instructions for deleting your data from BrewOS services."
  currentPath="/data-deletion"
>
  <section class="legal-page">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Data Deletion Instructions</h1>
      <p class="last-updated">Last updated: January 2025</p>

      <div class="content">
        <h2>How to Delete Your Data</h2>
        <p>
          BrewOS respects your right to control your personal data. You can request 
          deletion of your data at any time using one of the methods below.
        </p>

        <h2>Option 1: Delete via the App</h2>
        <p>The easiest way to delete your data is directly through the BrewOS app:</p>
        <ol>
          <li>Open the BrewOS web app at <a href="https://cloud.brewos.io">cloud.brewos.io</a></li>
          <li>Sign in to your account</li>
          <li>Go to <strong>Settings</strong></li>
          <li>Select <strong>Account</strong></li>
          <li>Click <strong>Delete Account</strong></li>
          <li>Confirm the deletion</li>
        </ol>
        <p>This will immediately delete your account and all associated data.</p>

        <h2>Option 2: Email Request</h2>
        <p>
          If you cannot access your account or prefer to contact us directly, 
          send an email to <a href="mailto:privacy@brewos.io">privacy@brewos.io</a> with:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Subject line: "Data Deletion Request"</li>
          <li>The email address associated with your BrewOS account</li>
          <li>A brief description of your request</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We will process your request within 30 days and send confirmation once complete.</p>

        <h2>What Data Gets Deleted</h2>
        <p>When you delete your account, we permanently remove:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Your account profile (email, name, profile picture)</li>
          <li>All device associations and configurations</li>
          <li>Session data and authentication tokens</li>
          <li>Push notification subscriptions</li>
          <li>Any brewing history and preferences stored in the cloud</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Data That May Be Retained</h2>
        <p>Some data may be retained for legitimate purposes:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Anonymized, aggregated analytics data</li>
          <li>Data required for legal compliance or fraud prevention</li>
          <li>Server logs (automatically deleted after 90 days)</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Local Device Data</h2>
        <p>
          Data stored locally on your BrewOS device (ESP32) is not affected by cloud 
          account deletion. To delete local device data:
        </p>
        <ol>
          <li>Connect to your device's local interface</li>
          <li>Go to <strong>Settings</strong> â†’ <strong>Factory Reset</strong></li>
          <li>Confirm to erase all local data and settings</li>
        </ol>

        <h2>Facebook Login Users</h2>
        <p>
          If you signed up using Facebook Login, you can also manage your data through 
          Facebook's settings:
        </p>
        <ol>
          <li>Go to your <a href="https://www.facebook.com/settings?tab=applications" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Facebook App Settings</a></li>
          <li>Find BrewOS in the list of apps</li>
          <li>Click to view or remove the app</li>
        </ol>
        <p>
          Note: Removing the app from Facebook does not automatically delete your BrewOS 
          account. Please also follow the deletion steps above to fully remove your data.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact Us</h2>
        <p>
          If you have any questions about data deletion, please contact us at:
          <a href="mailto:privacy@brewos.io">privacy@brewos.io</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    padding: 140px 0 80px;
    background: var(--cream-100);
  }

  .legal-page h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    font-weight: 800;
